- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on robotic grasping and manipulation.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the proposed framework utilizes visual information to train the control policies.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the framework is based on Deep Reinforcement Learning.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper addresses a problem in AI - robotic grasping from ungraspable poses.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper proposes a control policy for the robot arm to perform pregrasp manipulation.
